292
00:15:16,950 --> 00:15:17,830
Maybe.

293
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:21,240
You're more superficial than I thought.

294
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:26,590
I actually like whales

295
00:15:26,590 --> 00:15:28,000
because of Ding Ye too.

296
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,070
His first novel

297
00:15:29,070 --> 00:15:30,550
is called
"The Man Who Dreams of Whales".

298
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:32,550
After reading that novel,

299
00:15:32,830 --> 00:15:34,400
I learned about whale fall.

300
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,350
What is a whale fall?

301
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:40,350
A whale is the protector of the sea.

302
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,880
When it is alive,

303
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:45,710
it's a gentle yet immense presence.

304
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:47,160
After death,

305
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:49,640
its body will sink deep into the ocean

306
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,950
and become the warmest oasis
in the deep sea.

307
00:15:53,430 --> 00:15:55,160
It provides habitat

308
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:56,800
for countless sea creatures.

309
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:57,880
Food too.

310
00:15:58,160 --> 00:16:00,470
Sharks and grenadiers

311
00:16:00,470 --> 00:16:02,400
